    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The candlelight flickers low, much like the heavy, aching pulse in my very soul. He is gone... the promises, the vows, all nothing but ash in the wind. I look at the world and see only shadows, a gray shroud draped over everything I once loved. There is no warmth left in the sun, no music in the morning. It feels as though the stars themselves have turned their backs on me. I am so tired of carrying this silence. I feel as though I am already a ghost, merely waiting for the night to finally claim what is left of me.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
